This configuration is set on the default installation mode, such as IIS configuration and Python Vanilla in local disk C,
if you use another path please change the web.config and PATH according to your case

Python Configuration
1. Download and Install Python 3.6
2. Check if the python has already in the windows PATH Global environment C:\Python36\ and C:\Python36\Scripts
3. Install all requirement library, you can use install_lib.bat in the current directory (Step 3 requires step 2)

IIS and WSGI Configuration
Follow this tutorial
https://medium.com/@dpralay07/deploy-a-python-flask-application-in-iis-server-and-run-on-machine-ip-address-ddb81df8edf3#:~:text=To%20run%20a%20flask%20application,%E2%80%9Cpip%E2%80%9D%20command%20in%20CMD.&text=The%20Flask%20application%20connects%20with,expose%20the%20micro%2Dservice%20APIs.
In summary, you have to set WFASTCGI Enable and IIS Configuration
Notes: 
1. Do not add another website instead use the *Add Application* so your bot_url will be like this https://yourmachine.domain.com/mybot/
  mybot is the the name of your bot, you can change it and please rewrite bot's name in the config.yaml
2. Please add IIS Worker to your Application Pool
3. Please add IIS_USRS to your sharing permission folder if your script is not in inetpub 

WEBHOOK Telegram Configuration
1. open your web browser
2. type in address box "https://api.telegram.org/bot<bot_token>/setWebhook?url=<url_ngrok>&drop_pending_updates=True"
Notes: Please use https://yourmachine.domain.com
Note : you can skip this by using register_bot.bat (to start) or unregister_bot.bat (to stop) by config first in the config.yaml file